The paper deals with graph compression and distance preservation, which are topics related to data structures (cs.DS) and computational geometry (cs.CG). The use of minors and the study of trade-offs suggest that the paper may also fall under discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and graph theory (cs.GT). Finally, the mention of lower and upper bounds indicates that information theory (cs.IT) may also be relevant.
